We have 22 letters.

Perhaps the &amp;#39;x x&amp;#39; and &amp;#39;z&amp;#39; are overlapping.

But we need 11 pairs.

I think for this to work, we need to create 11 pairs from the 22 letters.

So let&amp;#39;s try pairing letters in order, taking two letters at a time.

1. m y

2. n z

3. n v

4. a a

